`docs/` holds two artifacts: a design decision log and a spec for future dylint lint rules, neither of which is summarized further up the tree — both are meant to be read directly, not skimmed via rollup.

DECISIONS.md is the authoritative append-only ADR log spanning the whole project (Rust lint/test regime, context pipeline, sandbox, user tools), documenting why architecture is the way it is, including the pivot from cage-based masking to opt-in context injection. DYLINT_RULES.md is forward-looking: none of its nine rules are implemented, and it explicitly cross-references live mechanical enforcement elsewhere in the repo (scripts/rationale_check.py for rule 1, scripts/cycle_check.sh for rule 4) as interim stand-ins to keep in sync until superseded.

Coupling to watch: changing CHANGES.md's format affects DYLINT_RULES.md's rule 5 design (public-surface stability baseline), and relaxing the `unreachable` restriction lint activates rule 9's exception. These are cross-repo dependencies documented here but not owned here.

No intent.md exists for this directory.